Steps Followed

Step 1: Create EKS Cluster
                eksctl create cluster --name my-cluster-jay --region us-east-1 --nodes 2

Step 2: Configure kubectl
                aws eks --region us-east-1 update-kubeconfig --name my-cluster-jay

Step 3: Verify Nodes
                kubectl get nodes

Step 4: Deploy Application
                kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml

Step 5: Expose Application
                kubectl apply -f service.yaml

Step 6: Verify Resources
                kubectl get pods
                kubectl get svc
                kubectl get endpoints

Step 7: Access Application
                http://<NODE-EXTERNAL-IP>:30007
